[{"location":"api/","page":"API Reference","title":"API Reference","text":"CurrentModule = Werks","category":"page"},{"location":"api/#API-Reference","page":"API Reference","title":"API Reference","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"api/#DataFrame-Utilities","page":"API Reference","title":"DataFrame Utilities","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"api/","page":"API Reference","title":"API Reference","text":"add_col_totals\nadd_row_totals\nadd_totals\ndrop_first\ndrop_last\nhead\ntail","category":"page"},{"location":"api/#Main.Werks.add_col_totals","page":"API Reference","title":"Main.Werks.add_col_totals","text":"add_col_totals(df::DataFrame; \n              total_col_name=\"Total\",\n              cols_to_sum=nothing)\n\nAdd a column of row totals to a DataFrame.\n\nArguments\n\ndf: Input DataFrame\ntotal_col_name: Name for the new column with row totals (default: \"Total\")\ncols_to_sum: Columns to include in summation (default: all numeric columns)\n\nReturns\n\nA new DataFrame with an additional column containing row totals\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"api/#Main.Werks.add_row_totals","page":"API Reference","title":"Main.Werks.add_row_totals","text":"add_row_totals(df::DataFrame; \n              total_row_name=\"Total\",\n              cols_to_sum=nothing)\n\nAdd a row of column totals to a DataFrame.\n\nArguments\n\ndf: Input DataFrame\ntotal_row_name: Label for the row with column totals (default: \"Total\")\ncols_to_sum: Columns to include in summation (default: all numeric columns)\n\nReturns\n\nA new DataFrame with an additional row containing column totals\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"api/#Main.Werks.add_totals","page":"API Reference","title":"Main.Werks.add_totals","text":"add_totals(df::DataFrame; \n          total_row_name=\"Total\", \n          total_col_name=\"Total\",\n          cols_to_sum=nothing)\n\nAdd both row and column totals to a DataFrame.\n\nArguments\n\ndf: Input DataFrame\ntotal_row_name: Label for the row with column totals (default: \"Total\")\ntotal_col_name: Name for the column with row totals (default: \"Total\")\ncols_to_sum: Columns to include in summation (default: all numeric columns)\n\nReturns\n\nA new DataFrame with both row and column totals added\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"api/#Main.Werks.drop_first","page":"API Reference","title":"Main.Werks.drop_first","text":"drop_first(df::DataFrame, n::Int=1)\n\nDelete the first n rows of a DataFrame.\n\nArguments\n\ndf: Input DataFrame\nn: Number of rows to delete (default: 1)\n\nReturns\n\nA new DataFrame with the first n rows removed\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"api/#Main.Werks.drop_last","page":"API Reference","title":"Main.Werks.drop_last","text":"drop_last(df::DataFrame, n::Int=1)\n\nDelete the last n rows of a DataFrame.\n\nArguments\n\ndf: Input DataFrame\nn: Number of rows to delete (default: 1)\n\nReturns\n\nA new DataFrame with the last n rows removed\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"api/#Main.Werks.head","page":"API Reference","title":"Main.Werks.head","text":"head(df::DataFrame, n::Int=6)\n\nDisplay the first n rows of a DataFrame.\n\nArguments\n\ndf: Input DataFrame\nn: Number of rows to display (default: 6)\n\nReturns\n\nA new DataFrame containing the first n rows\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"api/#Main.Werks.tail","page":"API Reference","title":"Main.Werks.tail","text":"tail(df::DataFrame, n::Int=6)\n\nDisplay the last n rows of a DataFrame.\n\nArguments\n\ndf: Input DataFrame\nn: Number of rows to display (default: 6)\n\nReturns\n\nA new DataFrame containing the last n rows\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"api/#GIS-and-Spatial-Utilities","page":"API Reference","title":"GIS and Spatial Utilities","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"api/","page":"API Reference","title":"API Reference","text":"dms_to_decimal","category":"page"},{"location":"api/#Main.Werks.dms_to_decimal","page":"API Reference","title":"Main.Werks.dms_to_decimal","text":"dms_to_decimal(coords::AbstractString) -> AbstractString\n\nConvert coordinates to decimal degrees format as a string.\n\nArguments\n\ncoords: A string representing the coordinates. Can be in one of two formats:\nDMS format: \"41° 15′ 31″ N, 95° 56′ 15″ W\"\nDecimal format: \"52.189902,-1.607106\"\n\nReturns\n\nA string containing the latitude and longitude coordinates in decimal degrees format, separated by a comma, e.g., \"41.258611111, -95.9375\".\n\nExample\n\n# DMS input\ncoord1 = \"41° 15′ 31″ N, 95° 56′ 15″ W\"\nresult1 = dms_to_decimal(coord1)\n# Output: \"41.258611111111111, -95.9375\"\n\n# Decimal input - returns as is with normalized formatting\ncoord2 = \"52.189902,-1.607106\"\nresult2 = dms_to_decimal(coord2)\n# Output: \"52.189902, -1.607106\"\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"api/#Visualization","page":"API Reference","title":"Visualization","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"api/","page":"API Reference","title":"API Reference","text":"cleveland_dot_plot\ncreate_bullseye_map","category":"page"},{"location":"api/#Main.Werks.cleveland_dot_plot","page":"API Reference","title":"Main.Werks.cleveland_dot_plot","text":"cleveland_dot_plot(df::DataFrame, value_col::Symbol, label_col::Symbol; \n                  xlabel::String=\"\", title::String=\"Cleveland Dot Plot\")\n\nCreate a Cleveland dot plot with polynomial trend line and reference features.\n\nArguments\n\ndf::DataFrame: Input DataFrame containing the data\nvalue_col::Symbol: Column name for the values to be plotted on x-axis\nlabel_col::Symbol: Column name for the labels to be shown on y-axis\nxlabel::String: Label for x-axis (default: \"\")\ntitle::String: Title for the plot (default: \"Cleveland Dot Plot\")\n\nFeatures\n\nSorts data by value in descending order\nAdds a 3rd-degree polynomial trend line\nShows 80% threshold line\nIncludes reference lines to y-axis\nFormats x-axis labels in thousands (K)\n\nReturns\n\nA Plots.Plot object\n\nExample\n\np = clevelanddotplot(nepop, :totalpopulation, :name,                        xlabel=\"Population\",                        title=\"Population of New England Counties\")\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"api/#Main.Werks.create_bullseye_map","page":"API Reference","title":"Main.Werks.create_bullseye_map","text":"create_bullseye_map(capital_name::String, capital_coords::String, \n                  file_path::String=\"bullseye.html\", \n                  bands::String=\"50, 100, 200\",\n                  color_scheme::Int=4)\n\nCreates an HTML file with a Leaflet map showing concentric circles around a center point.\n\nArguments\n\ncapital_name: Name of the central location to display in popup\ncapital_coords: Coordinates of the center point in DMS format\nfile_path: Path to save the HTML file (default: \"bullseye.html\")\nbands: Comma-separated distances for the concentric circles in miles (default: \"50, 100, 200\")\ncolor_scheme: Index of the color palette to use (1-5, default: 4)\n\nReturns\n\nPath to the created HTML file\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"api/#Package-Utilities","page":"API Reference","title":"Package Utilities","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"api/","page":"API Reference","title":"API Reference","text":"get_package_uuids","category":"page"},{"location":"api/#Main.Werks.get_package_uuids","page":"API Reference","title":"Main.Werks.get_package_uuids","text":"get_package_uuids(pkg_names::Vector{String}) -> Dict{String, UUID}\n\nGet UUIDs for multiple package names.\n\nArguments\n\npkg_names: Vector of package names to find UUIDs for\n\nReturns\n\nDictionary with package names as keys and UUIDs as values\nAny package names not found in dependencies will not be included in the result\n\nExample\n\nuuids = get_package_uuids([\"DataFrames\", \"CSV\", \"Plots\"])\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"api/","page":"API Reference","title":"API Reference","text":"","category":"page"},{"location":"function_index/","page":"Function Index","title":"Function Index","text":"CurrentModule = Werks","category":"page"},{"location":"function_index/#Function-Index","page":"Function Index","title":"Function Index","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"function_index/","page":"Function Index","title":"Function Index","text":"Modules = [Werks]","category":"page"},{"location":"function_index/","page":"Function Index","title":"Function Index","text":"","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"CurrentModule = Werks","category":"page"},{"location":"#Werks.jl","page":"Home","title":"Werks.jl","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"A collection of utility functions for data analysis and visualization in Julia","category":"page"},{"location":"#Overview","page":"Home","title":"Overview","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"Werks.jl provides a collection of utility functions for working with:","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"DataFrames (adding totals, dropping rows)\nGIS and spatial data (coordinate conversion, geometry operations)\nData visualization (Cleveland dot plots)\nJulia package management utilities","category":"page"},{"location":"#Installation","page":"Home","title":"Installation","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"using Pkg\nPkg.add(\"Werks\")","category":"page"},{"location":"#Quick-Start","page":"Home","title":"Quick Start","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"using Werks\n\n# Example: Create a dataframe with totals\nusing DataFrames\ndf = DataFrame(A = [1, 2, 3], B = [4, 5, 6], C = [\"a\", \"b\", \"c\"])\ndf_with_totals = add_totals(df)\n\n# Example: Get UUIDs for packages\npkg_uuids = get_package_uuids([\"DataFrames\", \"CSV\", \"Plots\"])\n\n# Example: Convert DMS coordinates to decimal\ncoords = \"41° 15′ 31″ N, 95° 56′ 15″ W\"\ndecimal_coords = dms_to_decimal(coords)","category":"page"},{"location":"#Features","page":"Home","title":"Features","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"DataFrame utilities: add_col_totals, add_row_totals, add_totals, drop_first, drop_last, head, tail\nCoordinate conversion: dms_to_decimal\nGIS utilities: count_coords, intersect_multipolygons\nVisualization: cleveland_dot_plot, create_bullseye_map\nMisc utilities: convert_to_integer!, gini, get_package_uuids","category":"page"},{"location":"#Authors","page":"Home","title":"Authors","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"Richard Careaga ","category":"page"}]
